{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T10:37:08.785Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fixing Bugs"},{"type":"text","text":" in coding workflows is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"structured, test-first process"},{"type":"text","text":" that prioritizes understanding the root cause before changing code, using automated tests to validate both the bug and the fix, and making minimal, targeted changes that don’t introduce regressions. The best practice is: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"reproduce the bug consistently → write a failing test → plan the fix → implement minimal changes → verify with tests → document the solution"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Bug fixing is the process of:\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Understanding the issue"},{"type":"text","text":": Get the exact error message or behavior description.\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reproducing the bug"},{"type":"text","text":": Identify the exact steps, inputs, and environment that cause it.\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Isolating the root cause"},{"type":"text","text":": Find which part of the code is responsible using debuggers, breakpoints, or logs.\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Planning the fix"},{"type":"text","text":": Design minimal changes that address the issue without creating new problems.\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Implementing the fix"},{"type":"text","text":": Write code that fixes the bug while following existing patterns.\n6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Verifying the fix"},{"type":"text","text":": Run tests to confirm the bug is fixed and no regressions exist.\n7. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Documenting"},{"type":"text","text":": Record what you found and how you fixed it."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without a structured approach:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You might fix the symptom, not the cause"},{"type":"text","text":": The bug returns later.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You might introduce regressions"},{"type":"text","text":": Your fix breaks other code.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You waste time"},{"type":"text","text":": Debugging becomes frustration instead of problem-solving.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You can’t prove the fix works"},{"type":"text","text":": No test to validate the bug is gone."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"With a structured approach:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You fix the root cause"},{"type":"text","text":": The bug doesn’t return.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You prevent regressions"},{"type":"text","text":": Tests catch new issues.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You save time"},{"type":"text","text":": Debugging is efficient and confident.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You can prove the fix works"},{"type":"text","text":": A failing test becomes a passing test."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of bug fixing as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"medical diagnosis"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Patient symptom"},{"type":"text","text":": The error message or bad behavior.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Diagnosis"},{"type":"text","text":": Find the root cause (which code is broken).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Treatment"},{"type":"text","text":": Apply the fix (minimal changes).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Follow-up"},{"type":"text","text":": Verify the patient is healthy (tests pass)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You don’t just give medicine (fix code) without diagnosing the problem (root cause analysis)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step-by-step workflow"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Phase 1: Understanding the Bug (MANDATORY)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 1.1: Initial Investigation"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Get the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"exact error message"},{"type":"text","text":" or behavior description.\n- Identify the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"affected module/function"},{"type":"text","text":" using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"grep"},{"type":"text","text":" or glob search.\n- Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"package_docs_search"},{"type":"text","text":" to understand intended behavior.\n- Check existing usage rules via "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"get_usage_rules"},{"type":"text","text":" or CLAUDE.md.\n- Search for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"similar issues"},{"type":"text","text":" in the codebase history."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 1.2: Root Cause Analysis"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Read the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"failing code and surrounding context"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Trace the execution path"},{"type":"text","text":" to see where the bug manifests.\n- Identify "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ALL places"},{"type":"text","text":" this bug might appear.\n- Determine if it’s a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"symptom of a larger issue"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Check for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"related bugs"},{"type":"text","text":" that might be hidden."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 1.3: Reproduce the Bug (MANDATORY)"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Write a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"failing test"},{"type":"text","text":" that demonstrates the bug.\n- Ensure the test fails for the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"RIGHT reason"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Verify the test will pass once the bug is fixed.\n- Place the test in the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"appropriate test file"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Run the test and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"capture the output"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Test template\ndef test_bug_reproduction():\n    # Setup: Create the conditions that cause the bug\n    result = buggy_function(input)\n    \n    # Assert: This should fail because of the bug\n    assert result == expected_value  # Currently fails"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Phase 2: Planning & Approval (MANDATORY)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 2.1: Create Fix Plan Document"},{"type":"text","text":"\nCreate a file like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<project_root>/notes/fixes/001-bug-description.md"},{"type":"text","text":" with:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Bug Summary"},{"type":"text","text":": 1–2 sentences describing the bug and impact.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Root Cause"},{"type":"text","text":": Technical explanation of why the bug occurs.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reproduction Test"},{"type":"text","text":": Paste the failing test.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Proposed Solution"},{"type":"text","text":": Detailed explanation of the fix approach.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Changes Required"},{"type":"text","text":": List of files and changes needed.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Regression Prevention"},{"type":"text","text":": How to ensure this doesn’t break again."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 2.2: Approval Checkpoint"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Present the fix plan with the failing test.\n- Ask: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"“I’ve reproduced the bug with a test. Should I proceed with this fix approach?”"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"WAIT for explicit approval"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Do NOT implement without approval"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Phase 3: Implementation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 3.1: Set Up Tracking"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"TodoWrite"},{"type":"text","text":" to track fix tasks.\n- Add an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"## Implementation Log"},{"type":"text","text":" section to the fix document.\n- Document each change as you make it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 3.2: Apply Fix"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Make "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"MINIMAL changes"},{"type":"text","text":" to fix the bug.\n- Do "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"NOT refactor unrelated code"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Follow "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"existing code patterns exactly"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Use framework patterns (e.g., Ash patterns) if touching framework code.\n- Add comments "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ONLY"},{"type":"text","text":" if fixing complex logic."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 3.3: Verification"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Run the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"reproduction test"},{"type":"text","text":" — MUST pass.\n- Run the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"full test suite"},{"type":"text","text":" — NO new failures.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Compile"},{"type":"text","text":" — NO new warnings.\n- Check for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"performance impact"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Verify "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"no security issues"},{"type":"text","text":" introduced."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 3.4: Extended Testing"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Test "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"edge cases"},{"type":"text","text":" around the fix.\n- Test "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"related functionality"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Verify the fix handles "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"all identified manifestations"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Run any "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"integration tests"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Phase 4: Documentation & Review"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 4.1: Update Fix Document"},{"type":"text","text":"\nAdd sections:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Final Implementation"},{"type":"text","text":": What was actually changed.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test Results"},{"type":"text","text":": Reproduction test (PASSING), full test suite (X passed, Y failed), new tests added.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Verification Checklist"},{"type":"text","text":": - [ ] Bug is fixed - [ ] No regressions introduced - [ ] Tests cover the fix - [ ] Code follows patterns"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 4.2: Final Review"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Show the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"passing test"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Summarize "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"what was fixed"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- List any "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"concerns"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Ask: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"“Fix implemented and tested. Ready to finalize?”"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Phase 5: Completion"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 5.1: Cleanup"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Ensure all tests are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"passing"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Remove any "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"debug code"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Update fix document with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"final status"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Mark all todos as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"complete"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 5.2: Prevention Follow-up"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Should "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"similar code"},{"type":"text","text":" be checked?\n- Is there a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"pattern to prevent this bug class"},{"type":"text","text":"?\n- Should "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"documentation"},{"type":"text","text":" be updated?\n- Note any "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"follow-up tasks"},{"type":"text","text":" needed."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key principles"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"TEST FIRST"},{"type":"text","text":": No fix without a failing test."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"MINIMAL CHANGES"},{"type":"text","text":": Fix only what’s broken, don’t refactor unrelated code."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"NO COMMITS"},{"type":"text","text":": Unless explicitly told to commit."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"VERIFY EVERYTHING"},{"type":"text","text":": All tests must pass."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"REPRODUCE FIRST"},{"type":"text","text":": Figure out the exact steps to reproduce the bug consistently."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ISOLATE THE BUG"},{"type":"text","text":": Use debuggers, breakpoints, or logs to find the exact location."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"DOCUMENT"},{"type":"text","text":": Keep notes about the bug, the solution, and lessons learned."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tools to use"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Debuggers"},{"type":"text","text":": Set breakpoints, inspect program state at different points."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Logging"},{"type":"text","text":": Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"console.log"},{"type":"text","text":" or logging to see which parts work."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Version control"},{"type":"text","text":": Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"git"},{"type":"text","text":" to track recent changes and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"git bisect"},{"type":"text","text":" to find when the bug was introduced."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Browser tools"},{"type":"text","text":": Use developer tools, console, inspector for web bugs."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Automated tests"},{"type":"text","text":": Unit tests, integration tests, end-to-end tests to verify the fix."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common mistakes"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fixing without reproducing"},{"type":"text","text":": You don’t know if the fix works."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fixing without a test"},{"type":"text","text":": You can’t prove the bug is gone."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Refactoring unrelated code"},{"type":"text","text":": You might break something else."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Skipping verification"},{"type":"text","text":": You don’t know if regressions exist."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not documenting"},{"type":"text","text":": You (or others) won’t understand the fix later."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best practices"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Write clean, readable code"},{"type":"text","text":": Use consistent formatting and avoid complicated logic."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Thorough testing"},{"type":"text","text":": Use automated tests to minimize bugs."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Version control"},{"type":"text","text":": Track important changes with Git."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Clear documentation"},{"type":"text","text":": Write comments and keep records of how things work."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Keep tools updated"},{"type":"text","text":": Regular updates prevent bugs from outdated components."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Ask for help"},{"type":"text","text":": Discuss with teammates or look for advice in community forums."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Take a break"},{"type":"text","text":": If stuck, go for a walk or sleep on the issue."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Bug fixing is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"structured, test-first process"},{"type":"text","text":": reproduce → test → plan → fix → verify → document."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Write a failing test first"},{"type":"text","text":" to prove the bug exists and the fix works."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Make "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"minimal changes"},{"type":"text","text":" that fix only what’s broken."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Verify with tests"},{"type":"text","text":": reproduction test passes, full test suite passes, no regressions."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Document the solution"},{"type":"text","text":": Record what you found and how you fixed it."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
